<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>17268</anchor>  <addr>jms-00A4</addr><route>jms-00A4.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>5</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" addr="jonmsterling" title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</link>’s cookbook</title>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>17269</anchor> <taxon>Recipe</taxon> <addr>jms-00A0</addr><route>jms-00A0.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>5</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Delicious numbing vinegar sauce</title>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>This sauce can be served over rice, noodles, dumplings, or fish.</p><ol><li>Take some Szechuan peppercorns and dried chili flakes (or dried chilis that you have shattered) and crush them lightly in a mortar and pestle.</li>
  <li>Toast the peppercorns and chili lightly in a hot pan.</li>
  <li>Fry the peppercorns and chili in plenty of oil.</li>
  <li>Fry some thinly chopped garlic without burning it.</li>
  <li>Mix all this together (including the oil), and mix in some salt, mirin, rice vinegar, and (optionally) a very small amount of black vineger, to taste. Feel free to add more oil if needed.</li>
  <li>Finely chop some coriander and mix it into the sauce.</li></ol></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>17270</anchor> <taxon>Person</taxon> <addr>jonmsterling</addr><route>jonmsterling.xml</route>    <title>Jon Sterling</title>   <meta name="external">https://www.jonmsterling.com/</meta><meta name="institution"><link href="camcl.xml" type="local" addr="camcl" title="Cambridge Computer Laboratory">Cambridge Computer Laboratory</link></meta><meta name="orcid">0000-0002-0585-5564</meta><meta name="position">Associate Professor</meta><meta name="phd-advisor">robertharper</meta><meta name="postdoc-advisor">larsbirkedal</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Associate Professor in Logical Foundations and Formal Methods at University of Cambridge. Formerly a <link href="jms-0061.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0061" title="TypeSynth: synthetic methods in program verification">Marie Skłodowska-Curie Postdoctoral Fellow</link> hosted at <link href="jms-00GC.xml" type="local" addr="jms-00GC" title="Aarhus University">Aarhus University</link> by <link href="larsbirkedal.xml" type="local" addr="larsbirkedal" title="Lars Birkedal">Lars Birkedal</link>, and before this a PhD student of <link href="robertharper.xml" type="local" addr="robertharper" title="Robert Harper">Robert Harper</link>.</p>
  
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
  
    
    
  
